      ],
      "updated": 1737658950552,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "* Analysing them is fine and simple once you\nhave the data\n\n* How do you get the data from a minimal\npoint of integration \n\n* getting user statistics will get me no where\n\n* i need to get where they stop \n(maybe how many times a component renders?.)\n- but with this i need to get control of the \nwhole code base\n\nwhere the scroll bar has been the longest is \nwhere i assume the user has watched the part\nfor the longest\n\nand for desktops , mouse tracking is easy , \n\n* display the data for mouse tracking \n (heatmaps is the best imo [same for mobile devs])",
      "fontSize": 11.954561801149932,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "* Analysing them is fine and simple once you\nhave the data\n\n* How do you get the data from a minimal\npoint of integration \n\n* getting user statistics will get me no where\n\n* i need to get where they stop \n(maybe how many times a component renders?.)\n- but with this i need to get control of the \nwhole code base\n\nwhere the scroll bar has been the longest is \nwhere i assume the user has watched the part\nfor the longest\n\nand for desktops , mouse tracking is easy , \n\n* display the data for mouse tracking \n (heatmaps is the best imo [same for mobile devs])",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
